approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5,05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the value {ERC20} uses, unless {_setupDecimals} is called. NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

params.amount0Desired: Max amount of token0 to deposit
params.amount1Desired: Max amount of token1 to deposit

returns.amount0: Amount of token0 deposited in vault
returns.amount1: Amount of token1 deposited in vault

getPositionDetails().details: Updates the position and return the updated reserves, fees & liquidity.

returns.amount0: Amount of token0 in the unipilot vault
returns.amount1: Amount of token1 in the unipilot vault
returns.baseLiquidity: The total liquidity of the base position
returns.fees0: Total amount of fees collected by unipilot position in terms of token0
returns.fees1: Total amount of fees collected by unipilot position in terms of token1
returns.rangeLiquidity: The total liquidity of the range position - N/A for active vault

returns._0: The first of the two tokens of the pool, sorted by address
returns._1: The second of the two tokens of the pool, sorted by address
returns._2: The pool's fee in hundredths of a bip, i.e. 1e-6
returns._3: The address of the Uniswap V3 Pool

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

pullLiquidity().details: Burns all the Unipilot position and HODL in the vault to prevent users from huge IL Only called by the selected operatorsUsers can also deposit/withdraw during HODL period.

readjustLiquidity(uint8).details: mints all amounts to this position(s) (including earned fees)For active vaults it can be called by the governance or operator, swaps imbalanced token and add all liquidity in base position.For passive vaults it can be called by any user. Two positions are placed - a base position and a limit position. The base position is placed first with as much liquidity as possible. This position should use up all of one token, leaving only the other one. This excess amount is then placed as a single-sided bid or ask position.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

toggleOperator(address).details: Must be called by the current governance

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. Requirements: - `sender` and `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - `sender` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``sender``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

uniswapV3MintCallback(uint256,uint256,by.details: In the implementation you must pay to the pool for the minted liquidity.

params.amount0Owed: The amount of token0 due to the pool for the minted liquidity
params.amount1Owed: The amount of token1 due to the pool for the minted liquidity
params.data: Any data passed through by the caller via the IUniswapV3PoolActions#mint call

uniswapV3SwapCallback(int256,int256,byte.details: In the implementation you must pay to the pool for swap.

params.amount0Delta: The amount of token0 due to the pool for the swap
params.amount1Delta: The amount of token1 due to the pool for the swap
params.data: Any data passed through by the caller via the IUniswapV3PoolActions#swap call

params.refundAsETH: whether to recieve in WETH or ETH (only valid for WETH/ALT pairs)

returns.amount0: Amount of token0 sent to recipient
returns.amount1: Amount of token1 sent to recipient

deposit(uint256,uint256,address).notice: Deposits tokens in proportion to the Unipilot's current holdings & mints them `Unipilot`s LP token.

getPositionDetails().notice: Calculates the vault's total holdings of TOKEN0 and TOKEN1 - in other words, how much of each token the vault would hold if it withdrew all its liquidity from Uniswap.

isOperator(address).notice: Returns the status for a given operator that can operate readjust & pull liquidity

readjustLiquidity(uint8).notice: Burns all position(s), collects any fees accrued and updates Unipilot's position(s)

toggleOperator(address).notice: Updates the status of given account as operator

uniswapV3MintCallback(uint256,uint256,by.notice: Pull in tokens from sender. Called to `msg.sender` after minting liquidity to a position from IUniswapV3Pool#mint.

uniswapV3SwapCallback(int256,int256,byte.notice: Called to `msg.sender` after minting swaping from IUniswapV3Pool#swap.

withdraw(uint256,address,bool).notice: Withdraws the desired shares from the vault with accumulated user fees and transfers to recipient.

@dev Amount of token0 held as unused balance.
@dev Amount of token1 held as unused balance.
@notice Verify that caller should be the address of a valid Uniswap V3 Pool
